HEADWORD: Toilsome
<hw>Toil"some</hw> <pr>(toil"s⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Attended
with toil, or fatigue and pain; laborious; wearisome; <as>as,
<ex>toilsome</ex> work</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What can be <qex>toilsome</qex> in these pleasant walks?</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Toil"some*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Toil"some*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toise</ent>⟦br⟧
